ruby script to modify locations table's region field.

requires:
  ruby 1.9.2
  rubygems
  mysql
  
$ cd path/to/app
      
If you don't already have a database with the sql loaded into it, create a database in mysql named mysql-test_development (if you want to use a different database name then change the database field in config/database.yml) and run the following command in bash:
  
  $ mysql -u username -p password mysql-test_development < data/import.sql 

Then after installing ruby 1.9.2 and rubygems run the following commands in bash while in the app directory
    
    $ gem install bundler
    $ bundle install
    $ bundle exec ruby-test.rb
    
    follow the prompts and enjoy
    